[00:00.89]When couples get married,
[00:03.78]they usually plan to have children.
[00:06.33]Sometimes however,
[00:08.36]a couple cannot have a child of their own.
[00:09.97]In this case, they may decide to adopt a child.
[00:13.91]In fact, adoption  is very common today.
[00:18.36]There are about 60,000 adoptions each year in the United States alone.
[00:23.83]Some people prefer to adopt infant.
[00:28.19]Others adopt older children.
[00:30.61]Some couples adopt children from their own countries.
[00:35.30]Others adopt children from foreign countries.
[00:39.81]In any case,
[00:41.61]they all adopt children for the same reason:
[00:43.93]they care about children and want to give their adopted child a happy life.
[00:51.68]Most adopted children know that they are adopted.
[00:56.53]Psychologists and childcare experts generally think this is a good idea.
[01:01.73]However,
[01:04.09]many adopted children or adoptees have very little information
